   The Burn's only score came on a penalty kick by Jorge Rodriguez
in the 82nd minute.
</P>
<P>
   New York-New Jersey beat Dallas 2-1 in overtime on Friday night
on Valencia's 100th-minute goal. The first team to five points
advances, with the MetroStars getting six points for two victories.
</P>
<P>
   The MetroStars will face either Chicago or New England in the
MLS semifinals. The decisive Game 3 of that series will be Friday
night in Chicago.
