Minnesota Twins 6-4.
</P>
<P>
   Sierra singled and scored on Scott Sheldon's homer in the ninth,
tying it at 3. Both teams scored a run in the 11th.
</P>
<P>
   Luis Alicea and Frank Catalanotto drew walks from Travis Miller
(1-3) in the Texas 12th and Sierra singled with one out.
Catalanotto later scored on a double steal.
</P>
<P>
   Sierra began the game 4-for-25 with one RBI since being called
up from the minors.
</P>
<P>
   John Wetteland (6-5) was the winning pitcher despite blowing his
ninth save chance of the season.
</P>
