<DOCNO> APW20000921.0037 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-21 01:42 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Stars 2, Coyotes 2, Tie  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX (AP) -- Rookie Ryan Lauzon scored the only even-strength
goal of the game at 8:36 of the third period, giving the Phoenix
Coyotes a 2-2 preseason tie with the Dallas Stars on Wednesday
night.
</P>
<P>
   Lauzon, Phoenix's fifth-round draft pick last year, scored on a
backhander from the slot as the Coyotes came from two goals down in
the final period.
</P>
<P>
   Jeremy Roenick scored a power-play goal at 4:44 of the third as
the Coyotes turned up the pressure.
</P>
<P>
   Dallas goalie Marty Turco made 17 of his 43 saves in the third
period and six more in overtime.
</P>
<P>
   Richard Matvichuk had a power-play goal for Dallas midway
through the first period, and Ryan Christie scored with a man
advantage with 4:03 left in the second.
</P>
<P>
   Sean Burke stopped 25 of Dallas' 27 shots.
</P>
<P>
   The Stars began the third period with a 5-on-3 advantage for
1:39, but couldn't score.
</P>
<P>
   Phoenix (2-1-1-1) got back in it on its fifth power play and
first of the third period when Joe Juneau sent the puck to Roenick
for a one-timer from the slot.
</P>
<P>
   The overtime was the first for Dallas, which split its first two
preseason contests, and the second for Phoenix. San Jose beat the
Coyotes 4-3 in overtime of their opener.
</P>
</TEXT>
