<HEADLINE> Mexico 2, Ecuador 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Enrique Meza won in his coaching debut for
Mexico as Jared Borgueti and Marco Antonio Ruiz each scored a goal
in a 2-0 exhibition victory over Ecuador on Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
   Meza, who guided Toluca to three straight championships in the
Mexican First Division, took over the reins of the national team
one week earlier following the resignation of Manuel Lapuente.
</P>
<P>
   The 20,507 fans at Qualcomm Stadium cheered loudly for Meza
during introductions.
</P>
<P>
   Victor Ruiz assisted on both goals, each coming on a corner kick
to set up a close-range header. The first came on Mexico's second
shot of the game in the 10th minute and the second came in the 60th
minute.
</P>
<P>
   Jorge Campos had to make only two saves for Mexico, which
matched Ecuador with 11 shots each. Ecuador's Jose Francisco
Cevallos had two stops.
</P>
<P>
   Borgueti nearly scored again in the 35th minute, when he caught
up with a bouncing pass in the penalty box, but his shot sailed
wide right.
</P>
<P>
   Ecuador's Marlon Ayovi drew a yellow card in the 36th minute for
tripping Daniel Osorno. Osorno again went down in the 55th minute
with a push from Geovanny Espinoza, who also received a caution.
</P>
<P>
   Meza's debut was made easier since Ecuador was without many top
players because of commitments to club teams. Among those missing
for Ecuador was two other players with Mexican ties, Agustin
Delgado and Alex Aguinaga, each with Necaxa.
</P>
<P>
   Mexico has one more tuneup against Peru on Wednesday in San
Jose, Calif., in preparation for the CONCACAF semifinals in Mexico
City on Oct. 8 against Trinidad &AMP; Tobago, which won its meeting in
qualifying play.
</P>
</TEXT>
