<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seminar To Focus on Harry Potter  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   HANOVER, Germany (AP) -- Harry Potter is going to school. Not
Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry, but the University of
Hanover.
</P>
<P>
   Professor Martin-Christoph Just plans to offer a seminar titled
''The Harry Potter Phenomenon'' starting in November to determine
the secret behind the success of the four-book series by author
J.K. Rowling.
</P>
<P>
   The class will look at whether the book is a totally new idea or
a remake on the idea of a ''poor orphan seeks his fortune''
combined with school stories and fantasy.
</P>
<P>
   Also discussed will be the ideological aspects of the book and
the marketing strategy that has rocketed it to the top of
best-seller lists all over the world.
</P>
<P>
   ''It is certain that these books satisfy the wishful imaginings
of readers that everyone can do magic,'' Just said Thursday.
</P>
</TEXT>
