<HEADLINE> Ray: Whitewater Findings Release OK  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Independent Counsel Robert Ray said a
Democratic senator is incorrect in criticizing Ray's public release
of findings in the Whitewater investigation.
</P>
<P>
   Sen. Carl Levin, D-Mich., said Ray's public airing of his
conclusions was unfair. Levin said they should be submitted under
seal to a federal appeals court when the prosecutor files a final
report in the Whitewater probe.
</P>
<P>
   ''There is nothing illegal, unfair or inappropriate about our
statement,'' said Ray, who found Wednesday that there was
insufficient evidence to prove that either President Clinton or his
wife committed a crime in the Whitewater scandal.
</P>
<P>
   Ray said the Independent Counsel statute was rewritten six years
ago to allow for a public explanation of a prosecutor's decision
not to indict someone.
</P>
</TEXT>
