<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Senate approves bill to increase legal age to buy handguns  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   TRENTON, N.J. (AP) - The Senate on Thursday approved a plan to
increase the legal age to buy handguns in New Jersey to 21.
</P>
<P>
   The unanimous vote is aimed at eliminating a conflict between
New Jersey's regulations and federal law, bill sponsors said.
</P>
<P>
   The current legal age to buy a handgun is 18. The bill passed
Thursday provides exemptions for law enforcement officials who are
under 21 but have been trained in using firearms.
</P>
<P>
   Anyone under the proposed legal age who carried a handgun would
face up to 18 months in prison and fines of $10,000 under the bill,
S-2047.
</P>
<P>
   A similar measure passed the Assembly on June 26 by a vote of
70-7 and cleared the Senate 38-0 on May 18.
</P>
<P>
   Full text of bills available at the Office of Legislative
Services Web site located at http://www.njleg.state.nj.us
</P>
</TEXT>
