<HEADLINE> Man charged with making false water tampering report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) - A Manhattan man who claimed to have felt a
burning sensation after drinking from a bottle of water has been
charged with making a false report, police said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Eduardo Pardo bought a bottle of Poland Spring water from an
Audubon Avenue grocery store on Sept. 14. Authorities accused him
of then going to a gym on Broadway, where he allegedly mixed bleach
with the water.
</P>
<P>
   Pardo then drank the water, then complained of a burning
sensation and was taken to a hospital for treatment.
</P>
<P>
   Making a false report is a misdemeanor, and Pardo faces up to a
year in jail if convicted.
</P>
<P>
   Authorities have been investigating a rash of potential water
tampering cases in the metropolitan area, but have yet to find any
evidence of foul play.
