Red Sox 9, Indians 8, Game 1
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   BOSTON (AP) -- A day after getting swept by Cleveland, the Boston Red Sox
overcame a seven-run, first-inning deficit and beat the Indians 9-8 today in the
opener of another day-night doubleheader. Boston scored twice in the first, then
took the lead when Justin Speier (4-2) walked Jose Offerman with the
bases-loaded in a six-run third.
AP NewsBrief By KRISTEN DE GROOT 
