<HEADLINE> Tampa Bay LW Suspended Indefinitely  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- Tampa Bay left wing Gordie Dwyer was
suspended by the NHL on Thursday, pending a hearing, for his fight
with Washington's Joe Reekie on Sept. 19.
</P>
<P>
   Dwyer and Reekie, a former Tampa Bay defenseman, fought during
the third period of the teams' 4-4 exhibition tie. Dwyer received
minor penalties for charging and roughing, a 10-minute misconduct
and two game misconducts. Reekie received a 10-minute misconduct
and a game misconduct.
</P>
<P>
   Tampa Bay general manager Rick Dudley said Dwyer could receive a
long suspension.
</P>
<P>
   ''What I told Gordie, it's done. There's nothing you can do
about that,'' Dudley said. ''It happened. It was a mistake.''
</P>
<P>
   Dwyer was suspended until a hearing is conducted. No date for
the hearing has been set.
</P>
<P>
   The Lightning added defenseman Mel Angelstad, who has recorded
more than 400 penalty minutes twice in an eight-year minor league
career, to their training camp roster.
</P>
<P>
   Tampa Bay also returned Nikita Alexeev, the team's first-round
pick in the 2000 draft, to Erie of the Ontario Hockey League.
Forwards Nils Ekman and Thomas Ziegler were sent to Detroit of the
International Hockey League.
</P>
